'''''Star Wars Insider'' 98''' is the 98th issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', and the 6th issue to be published by [[Titan Magazines]].

{{Magazine-stub|issue}}

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"Editor's Welcome" {{C|by [[Brian J. Robb]]}}
*"[[Com-Scan]]"
*"[[Best of StarWars.com]]"
*"[[Jawa's Corner]]"
**Books &mdash; [[Legacy of the Force: Fury|''Fury'']] Unleashed Upon the Galaxy {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
**Comics &mdash; Plotting the [[Star Wars: Vector|''Vector'']] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
**Toys &mdash; Bringing Battlefront to Life! {{C|by Frank Parisi}}
**[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] &mdash; "Like Something Out of a Dream" {{C|by [[Leland Chee]]}}
**[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Rancho Obi-Wan Reunion Tops off a Busy Year {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
**[[International Collecting]] &mdash; Sweden {{C|by [[Gus Lopez]]}}
**[[Set Piece]] &mdash; Massassi Temple Throne Room {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
**[[Padawan's Corner]]" &mdash; How to Draw: An Ewok {{C|by [[Cynthia Narcisi|Cynthia Cummens]]}}
**[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 29 {{C|by [[Mary Franklin]]}}
**[[Indy Vault]] #6 {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler|J. W. Rinzler]]}}
**[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]

===Features===
*"[[Roger Christian: Galaxy Builder]]"
*:<small>Set decorator Roger Christian won an Oscar for his work in bringing the ''Star Wars'' galaxy to the screen.</small>
*"[[Ben Burtt: Can You Hear the Force?]]
*:<small>''Star Wars Insider'' meets the man behind the unique sounds of the ''Star Wars'' galaxy, [[Ben Burtt]].</small>
*"[[The Man Who Sold Star Wars|The Man Who Sold ''Star Wars''!]]"
*:<small>In 1976 [[Charles Lippincott]] led a word-of-mouth campaign to promote a forthcoming little-known movie called ''Star Wars''.</small>
*"[[Pirates of the Boards]]: Part 6"
*:<small>Our exclusive series of ''Star Wars'' storyboards draws to a conclusion as Luke attacks the Death Star!</small>
*"[[Fabric of the Universe]]"
*:<small>Over 30 years ago, [[John Mollo]] faced the task of clothing an entire galaxy as he began work on the first ''Star Wars'' movie.</small>
*"[[Star Players]]"
*:<small>They're the unsung heroes of the original ''Star Wars'': Meet Fixer, the original Wedge, Greedo, and Biggs!</small>

==Release and reception==
According to TFAW.com, ''Insider'' #97 was originally scheduled to be the "Special Effects" issue; however, that issue was most likely postponed until #98, while [[Star Wars Insider 97|#97]] is the "[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] & [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]]" issue.<ref name="TFAW">{{WebCite|url=http://www.tfaw.com/Profile/Star-Wars-Insider-97-(Newsstand-Edition)___285151|text=Star Wars Insider #97 (Newsstand Edition)|archivedate=20151231160719}}</ref>

